modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve a fixed string, split a file path into chunks, and access a predefined list of file names. Operates on strings and lists of strings. Used to extract configuration values, process file paths, and access static file metadata.
Reads and returns the contents of a file given its path as a string. Operates on file paths and raw text data. Useful for loading configuration files or processing log entries.

Handles application entry point by initializing system components and launching the primary execution loop. Operates on unit type to signal program start and completion. Used to bootstrap the application and manage its lifecycle.

Extracts configuration values from fixed strings, splits file paths into components, and accesses predefined file lists. Operates on strings and lists of strings, offering functions for string retrieval, path splitting, and metadata access. Examples include parsing directory structures, validating configuration entries, and generating file listings. Supports direct manipulation of textual data and structured file information.

Provides functions to retrieve the version string, optional commit hash, and optional commit date. Works with string and option types to expose build-time metadata. Used to dynamically access build information in logging, diagnostics, and deployment tracking.

Processes m4 macro-based test scripts from GNU Autoconf, executing them in a controlled environment. Handles test cases structured as shell scripts with embedded m4 directives, extracting and running individual test commands. Supports isolated execution of test fragments for debugging and validation.

Loads and processes file content, manages application startup, parses configuration and file paths, and retrieves build metadata. Operates on strings, lists, and option types to handle text, file structures, and version data. Enables tasks such as reading config files, splitting paths, extracting version info, and generating file listings. Supports dynamic access to build details and facilitates file-based data manipulation.
